<p><b>Gun politics in <a href="/wiki/Switzerland" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a></b> are unique in Europe. The personal weapon of militia personnel is kept at home as part of the military obligations. This, in addition to liberal gun laws and strong shooting traditions, has led to a very high gun count per capita. Switzerland has one of the highest gun ownership rates in the world. In recent times political opposition has expressed a desire for tighter gun regulations.<sup id="cite_ref-SPIEGEL_ONLINE_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-SPIEGEL_ONLINE-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
